text: Natukhay () is a rural locality (an aul) in Takhtamukayskoye Rural Settlement of Takhtamukaysky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 330 as of 2018. There are 10 streets. == Geography == The aul is located 6 km south from Takhtamukay. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Natukhajs. == References == Category:Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District
title: Natukhay
